    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (78.25) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) headline the squad, both benefiting significantly from a favorable matchup against Luis Severino and Cristian Javier, respectively. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** earns a massive boost from the SP skill projection and his dynamic platoon advantage, while **Mickey Moniak** is positioned for a breakout performance thanks to a 14% park factor upgrade and an 8% boost for batting second in the order. **James Wood** also earns a high-tier nod (73.87) as the leadoff man against Michael McGreevy; the combination of a positive park factor and a solid 14% boost for facing a lower-tier pitcher makes him an essential start for our SB-hungry team.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Max Muncy**, who finished with a 52.65, just barely missing the cut behind the more efficient matchup profiles of our bottom-tier starters. While **Max Muncy** provides power, the optimizer favored **Kyle Karros** (54.54) for his park-induced ceiling against Cristian Javier. Meanwhile, **Brice Turang** (50.94) remains the most notable omission; despite the high-leverage leadoff spot, his score was suppressed by a tough matchup against Sonny Gray and an \"Elite Hold\" warning on opposing catchers, which creates significant risk for his stolen base production. We are closely monitoring the lineups for **Gabriel Moreno**, **Josh Naylor**, and **Jose Caballero**, as the current projections rely on estimated spots; should these hitters drop lower in their respective lineups, we may see their efficiency scores dip below the 50-point threshold. \n\nWe are playing a high-upside strategy today, leaning on the speed and park factors for **Corbin Carroll** (63.31) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (64.69) to keep our daily efficiency trending upward. **Trevor Story** remains a start at 57.96, though we are tracking the wind-in warning at his stadium, which slightly dampens his HR potential. We will keep **Austin Riley**, **Vinnie Pasquantino**, and **Brice Turang** on high alert, ready to pivot if any of our active starters are scratched or if pinch-hitting opportunities for **Seiya Suzuki**, **Carson Williams**, **Alex Freeland**, **Gabriel Arias**, or **Travis Bazzana** emerge in late-day defensive adjustments.",
